280
00:21:59,790 --> 00:22:02,510
If she often feels tired

281
00:22:02,960 --> 00:22:03,960
and has a poor appetite,

282
00:22:04,240 --> 00:22:06,240
and the bruises won’t heal,

283
00:22:06,720 --> 00:22:08,880
I suggest she go to
a big hospital for a checkup.

284
00:22:20,830 --> 00:22:21,680
Yuan.

285
00:22:21,680 --> 00:22:23,440
Where did you go?
I’ve been looking for you.

286
00:22:24,070 --> 00:22:25,030
What’s wrong?

287
00:22:27,240 --> 00:22:30,030
Yuan, let me see your math paper.

288
00:22:30,030 --> 00:22:31,830
I slept last night and didn’t write it.

289
00:22:31,830 --> 00:22:33,270
Write it yourself first.

290
00:22:35,750 --> 00:22:37,110
Just let me see it for once.

291
00:22:37,110 --> 00:22:39,400
The last time. Just for once.

292
00:22:39,400 --> 00:22:41,070
You either sleep
or read comics every day.

293
00:22:41,070 --> 00:22:43,200
Do you know you are
a student of Grade 3?

294
00:22:43,200 --> 00:22:44,200
The college entrance examination
is six months later.

295
00:22:44,200 --> 00:22:46,400
Are you going to see
my math paper at the time, Han Yayi?

296
00:22:56,750 --> 00:22:57,590
What’s wrong?

297
00:22:59,310 --> 00:23:01,920
It’s just a paper.
Don’t you always let her see it?

298
00:23:01,920 --> 00:23:03,310
Why are you so angry today?

299
00:23:38,880 --> 00:23:39,640
Yuan Caixi.

300
00:23:39,640 --> 00:23:41,240
-Stop chasing me.
-Yuan Caixi.

301
00:23:43,000 --> 00:23:43,920
What’s happening?

302
00:23:44,790 --> 00:23:45,800
You run so fast

303
00:23:46,000 --> 00:23:47,030
and you don’t let me chase you?

304
00:23:52,480 --> 00:23:53,160
Fine.

305
00:23:53,510 --> 00:23:54,510
I won’t chase you.

306
00:23:55,750 --> 00:23:56,920
But you need to tell me
what’s wrong with you.

307
00:23:59,680 --> 00:24:00,480
Nothing.

308
00:24:04,590 --> 00:24:05,550
By the way,

309
00:24:06,550 --> 00:24:08,000
do you have a match two days later?

310
00:24:08,480 --> 00:24:09,750
Yeah, it’s the day after tomorrow.

311
00:24:10,960 --> 00:24:11,920
Are you really okay?

312
00:24:12,510 --> 00:24:14,270
I’m fine. I don’t know
what’s wrong with me recently.

313
00:24:14,270 --> 00:24:15,440
I think there is too much on my mind.

314
00:24:15,880 --> 00:24:16,750
Don’t be sad.

315
00:24:16,750 --> 00:24:17,480
Go back to class.

316
00:24:18,350 --> 00:24:18,960
Yeah.

317
00:24:35,270 --> 00:24:37,110
Which question? I’ll teach you.

318
00:24:38,920 --> 00:24:40,310
Are you not angry with me anymore?

319
00:24:42,790 --> 00:24:43,590
You are not angry anymore.

320
00:24:43,590 --> 00:24:44,680
How can I be angry?

321
00:24:47,240 --> 00:24:48,440
That’s great.

322
00:24:49,400 --> 00:24:51,510
Sorry that I lost my temper.

323
00:24:51,960 --> 00:24:54,270
I guess I’m too stressed recently.

324
00:24:55,270 --> 00:24:56,200
It’s okay.

325
00:24:56,920 --> 00:25:00,110
Yuan, considering how sad I’m,

326
00:25:01,790 --> 00:25:03,310
write the paper for me

327
00:25:03,310 --> 00:25:04,680
to redeem yourself.

328
00:25:04,920 --> 00:25:06,790
I won’t beat you if you
get your hands off me.

329
00:25:06,790 --> 00:25:08,000
No problem.

330
00:25:11,350 --> 00:25:12,000
Here.

331
00:25:17,270 --> 00:25:18,470
Does your family run a mini mart?

332
00:25:18,470 --> 00:25:19,880
You give her strawberry milk every day.

333
00:25:21,790 --> 00:25:23,920
I heard that sweet food
can relieve stress.

334
00:25:30,510 --> 00:25:31,750
It’s okay, Monitor.

335
00:25:32,640 --> 00:25:34,880
I’ll bring you a box of milk
from my house.

336
00:25:38,000 --> 00:25:39,110
Thank you.

337
00:25:40,110 --> 00:25:41,240
It’s nice to have you.

338
00:25:41,240 --> 00:25:42,030
You’re welcome.

339
00:25:44,030 --> 00:25:45,110
Am I the most handsome man?

340
00:25:49,070 --> 00:25:49,790
Yuan.

341
00:25:50,270 --> 00:25:52,350
Kinship is a paddle
and friendship is a sail.

342
00:25:52,590 --> 00:25:56,000
Let’s travel on the ocean of
the college entrance examination!

343
00:25:56,270 --> 00:25:58,440
-Well-said!
-Bravo!

344
00:26:03,310 --> 00:26:04,750
Write the homework. Hurry up.

345
00:27:13,750 --> 00:27:14,640
Zeyu?

346
00:27:14,640 --> 00:27:16,720
Shouldn’t you be
in the classroom right now?

347
00:27:17,310 --> 00:27:19,440
I just want to be
in a different environment.

348
00:27:20,310 --> 00:27:21,440
Your book.

349
00:27:21,440 --> 00:27:22,070
Thank you.

350
00:27:24,620 --> 00:27:26,620
(Secrets of Blood)

351
00:27:30,200 --> 00:27:32,270
You can take it. I’ll find another book.

352
00:27:32,270 --> 00:27:34,070
Did your father die of leukemia?

353
00:27:36,440 --> 00:27:38,200
Han Yayi said you have
lost your appetite recently.

354
00:27:38,720 --> 00:27:39,790
You even fainted

355
00:27:40,750 --> 00:27:42,110
more than once.

356
00:27:43,270 --> 00:27:44,310
Don’t take a wild guess.

357
00:27:46,440 --> 00:27:47,590
I never take a wild guess.

358
00:27:49,110 --> 00:27:50,960
I said it’s just a friend of mine.

359
00:27:53,350 --> 00:27:55,400
If my judgment is right...

360
00:27:58,920 --> 00:27:59,750
Where else?

361
00:28:00,680 --> 00:28:01,640
Ning Zeyu!

362
00:28:04,640 --> 00:28:05,640
What’s wrong?

363
00:28:05,640 --> 00:28:06,440
I don’t know.

364
00:28:06,440 --> 00:28:08,160
Aren’t they the two
straight A students in Class 2?

365
00:28:08,510 --> 00:28:10,550
Oh, Zeyu and monitor are having a fight.

366
00:28:11,270 --> 00:28:12,030
Come with me.

367
00:28:19,240 --> 00:28:20,070
Ning Zeyu!

368
00:28:21,790 --> 00:28:22,880
Get off me!

369
00:28:26,000 --> 00:28:26,720
Did you go to the hospital?

370
00:28:26,720 --> 00:28:27,750
Why should I go to the hospital?

371
00:28:27,750 --> 00:28:28,830
I said it’s a friend of mine.

372
00:28:28,830 --> 00:28:29,790
Even Li He won’t believe it.

373
00:28:29,790 --> 00:28:31,480
-It’s really a friend of mine.
-Which friend?

374
00:28:31,480 --> 00:28:33,240
As far as I know, you only have
one friend, Han Yayi.

375
00:28:33,240 --> 00:28:35,070
Is it Han Yayi?
Does Han Yayi have leukemia?

376
00:28:35,070 --> 00:28:35,590
Don’t curse her.

377
00:28:35,590 --> 00:28:36,480
Who is that then?

378
00:28:47,830 --> 00:28:48,880
Did you go to the hospital?

379
00:28:51,030 --> 00:28:51,880
No.

380
00:28:53,720 --> 00:28:54,510
Why?

381
00:28:57,790 --> 00:28:58,790
I’m scared.

382
00:29:03,510 --> 00:29:04,590
Does Aunt know it?

383
00:29:06,830 --> 00:29:10,170
My mother, Yuan Haoxi, Li He

384
00:29:10,520 --> 00:29:12,000
and Han Yayi, they all have no idea.

385
00:29:12,000 --> 00:29:14,030
If I hadn’t met you today,
no one would know it.

386
00:29:14,030 --> 00:29:15,720
Yuan Caixi, what are you thinking about?

387
00:29:15,720 --> 00:29:16,400
It’s such an important thing.

388
00:29:16,400 --> 00:29:18,070
Don’t you think you should
talk to your family first?

389
00:29:18,070 --> 00:29:19,070
How should I tell them?

390
00:29:19,750 --> 00:29:21,400
My dad died of leukemia.

391
00:29:21,830 --> 00:29:23,200
How should I tell this to my mom?

392
00:29:23,920 --> 00:29:25,480
Tell her that I got
the same disease as my dad?

393
00:29:25,480 --> 00:29:27,350
How will my mom take it?
She will go crazy!

394
00:29:27,350 --> 00:29:29,440
But keeping it from her
can’t solve the problem.

395
00:29:30,270 --> 00:29:31,140
It’s leukemia.

396
00:29:31,140 --> 00:29:33,030
It’s not a cold or any minor illness.

397
00:29:33,510 --> 00:29:35,550
You can’t get treatment
if you don’t say it.

398
00:29:45,030 --> 00:29:46,480
What should I do with you?

399
00:29:51,070 --> 00:29:52,550
I don’t know what to do.

400
00:29:59,750 --> 00:30:00,920
Zeyu.

401
00:30:01,400 --> 00:30:02,750
Can you promise me one thing?

402
00:30:05,550 --> 00:30:07,270
Fine. Go ahead.

403
00:30:09,070 --> 00:30:10,070
Keep it a secret for me.

404
00:30:10,720 --> 00:30:12,720
You must keep it a secret for me.

405
00:30:12,720 --> 00:30:14,200
You can’t tell anyone, especially Li He.

406
00:30:14,440 --> 00:30:15,720
He is going to have a match.

407
00:30:16,480 --> 00:30:17,880
I can’t affect him.

408
00:30:17,880 --> 00:30:19,310
I’m not important. His match
is the most important thing.

409
00:30:19,310 --> 00:30:20,160
Can you do it?

410
00:30:23,270 --> 00:30:24,400
Please.

411
00:30:28,110 --> 00:30:29,110
I’m begging you.

412
00:30:40,750 --> 00:30:41,440
Fine.

413
00:30:43,110 --> 00:30:44,070
To the end of the month.

414
00:30:45,070 --> 00:30:46,510
I’ll keep it secret for you
only to the end of the month.

415
00:30:47,960 --> 00:30:49,480
If you don’t go to
the hospital next month,

416
00:30:50,070 --> 00:30:51,720
-I will tell them for you.
-Okay.

417
00:30:54,160 --> 00:30:55,750
Let’s go. Let me take you back.

418
00:31:01,240 --> 00:31:02,810
I put the key at the door of
the broadcasting room.

419
00:31:02,810 --> 00:31:03,640
It’s under the mat.

420
00:31:03,640 --> 00:31:05,310
Remember to take it tomorrow.

421
00:31:10,000 --> 00:31:10,880
Are you all right?

422
00:31:11,270 --> 00:31:12,160
I’m fine. Let’s go.

423
00:31:16,160 --> 00:31:17,550
What’s happening?

424
00:31:53,550 --> 00:31:55,200
You can’t keep a secret forever.

425
00:31:55,200 --> 00:31:56,240
It’s better to say it earlier.

426
00:32:03,000 --> 00:32:03,750
Li He.

427
00:32:07,720 --> 00:32:08,680
I’ve been waiting for you for a while.

428
00:32:09,200 --> 00:32:10,350
Didn’t you go to the library?

429
00:32:10,350 --> 00:32:11,720
I didn’t find you.

430
00:32:12,070 --> 00:32:12,830
Where have you been?

431
00:32:15,830 --> 00:32:17,880
There are a few questions
I don’t know how to solve.

432
00:32:17,880 --> 00:32:19,160
So I went back to ask Zeyu.

433
00:32:22,310 --> 00:32:23,030
Have you finished?

434
00:32:23,030 --> 00:32:24,350
-Yeah.
-Can I take you home?

435
00:32:25,110 --> 00:32:25,790
Yeah.

436
00:32:26,160 --> 00:32:26,880
Okay.

437
00:32:27,000 --> 00:32:27,640
Let’s go.

438
00:32:28,110 --> 00:32:28,720
Bye.

439
00:32:29,270 --> 00:32:30,400
-Let’s go.
-Yeah.

440
00:32:56,550 --> 00:32:58,400
What questions did you ask Ning Zeyu?

441
00:33:00,790 --> 00:33:03,200
Different values of X should be solved

442
00:33:03,200 --> 00:33:05,000
by different analytic functions.

443
00:33:06,110 --> 00:33:07,350
Piecewise function?

444
00:33:08,070 --> 00:33:09,400
That’s all you asked?

445
00:33:09,830 --> 00:33:10,350
Yeah.

446
00:33:10,640 --> 00:33:11,750
I left after I asked him.

447
00:33:13,000 --> 00:33:13,750
It sounds right.

448
00:33:14,680 --> 00:33:16,000
Ning Zeyu spends all his time

449
00:33:16,000 --> 00:33:18,830
doing homework or writing programs.

450
00:33:20,110 --> 00:33:22,680
There should be nothing else he can say.

451
00:33:23,400 --> 00:33:24,070
Let’s go.

452
00:33:37,720 --> 00:33:38,790
Rest early tonight.

453
00:33:39,200 --> 00:33:40,440
I’ll pick you up tomorrow morning.

454
00:33:40,720 --> 00:33:41,510
Well, you don’t need to.

455
00:33:42,480 --> 00:33:43,510
Why not?

456
00:33:44,640 --> 00:33:46,790
Aren’t you going to have a match?

457
00:33:46,790 --> 00:33:48,200
Just stay focused on
preparing for the match.

458
00:33:48,200 --> 00:33:49,240
You don’t need to pick me up.

459
00:33:50,790 --> 00:33:52,160
Picking you up won’t affect the match.

460
00:33:53,030 --> 00:33:54,200
But...

461
00:33:54,750 --> 00:33:55,880
There is no but.

462
00:33:57,550 --> 00:33:58,480
Yuan Caixi.

463
00:33:59,350 --> 00:34:01,110
You are you. The game is the game.

464
00:34:01,310 --> 00:34:02,680
There is no conflict between you two.

465
00:34:02,680 --> 00:34:04,270
Whether there is a game or not,

466
00:34:04,270 --> 00:34:06,350
I will pick you up and take you home.

467
00:34:07,720 --> 00:34:08,590
Do you hear me?

468
00:34:14,920 --> 00:34:15,880
What are you looking at?

469
00:34:16,320 --> 00:34:18,070
You don’t want to go home
or you don’t want to leave me?

470
00:34:19,230 --> 00:34:20,030
Let’s go.

471
00:34:22,760 --> 00:34:23,710
The weather is great.

472
00:34:25,880 --> 00:34:26,880
The moon is really round.

473
00:34:29,920 --> 00:34:32,440
Tell Chief. Don’t tell Chief.

474
00:34:33,670 --> 00:34:35,070
Tell Chief.

475
00:34:35,710 --> 00:34:36,590
Don’t tell Chief.

476
00:34:38,070 --> 00:34:40,960
Tell Chief. Don’t tell Chief.

477
00:34:56,140 --> 00:35:00,260
(Chuan)

478
00:35:04,190 --> 00:35:05,670
What if I think too much about it?

479
00:35:07,000 --> 00:35:08,630
I must be thinking too much about it.

480
00:35:27,300 --> 00:35:28,700
(Chief)

481
00:35:32,590 --> 00:35:33,440
Hello, Chief.

482
00:35:33,840 --> 00:35:34,670
Hello, Chuan.

483
00:35:35,110 --> 00:35:36,110
Why did you call me?

484
00:35:37,760 --> 00:35:40,190
Nothing, actually.

485
00:35:40,800 --> 00:35:41,960
What is nothing?

486
00:35:43,590 --> 00:35:45,590
Well... it’s...

487
00:35:45,590 --> 00:35:46,920
Just say it.

488
00:35:46,920 --> 00:35:48,280
I need to get up early tomorrow.

489
00:35:48,840 --> 00:35:50,210
I will buy breakfast for monitor

490
00:35:50,290 --> 00:35:52,230
and then send her to school.

491
00:35:52,230 --> 00:35:52,920
Chief.

492
00:35:54,670 --> 00:35:56,880
I saw monitor and Zeyu together again.

493
00:35:57,440 --> 00:35:58,150
And then?

494
00:35:58,960 --> 00:35:59,760
Then?

495
00:36:00,230 --> 00:36:03,550
I said that I saw them together again.

496
00:36:05,360 --> 00:36:07,510
Chuan, are you stupid?

497
00:36:07,510 --> 00:36:08,440
We are at the same school.

498
00:36:08,440 --> 00:36:10,360
What’s so strange to see them together?

499
00:36:10,760 --> 00:36:12,880
When you were running
during the night classes,

500
00:36:12,880 --> 00:36:15,630
I saw them talking very intimately.

501
00:36:16,070 --> 00:36:17,510
Were they near the library?

502
00:36:17,800 --> 00:36:19,920
Yes, near the library.

503
00:36:21,670 --> 00:36:23,150
She told me about it.

504
00:36:23,840 --> 00:36:26,320
She was going to study near the library.

505
00:36:26,320 --> 00:36:28,960
Later, there was a math problem
she couldn’t solve.

506
00:36:28,960 --> 00:36:30,630
So she went to ask Zeyu.

507
00:36:30,630 --> 00:36:31,510
What’s wrong?

508
00:36:31,510 --> 00:36:32,550
No way.

509
00:36:33,110 --> 00:36:34,880
Ask him a math problem in that place?

510
00:36:37,360 --> 00:36:39,840
You don’t understand
the world of straight A students.

511
00:36:39,840 --> 00:36:41,320
Stop guessing.

512
00:36:44,070 --> 00:36:44,620
Chief.

513
00:36:45,180 --> 00:36:47,840
Do you believe whatever
Yuan Caixi told you?

514
00:36:47,840 --> 00:36:49,920
Yeah, she won’t lie to me.

515
00:36:53,150 --> 00:36:55,030
All right, there is nothing else.

516
00:36:55,360 --> 00:36:56,360
Chief, good night.

517
00:37:05,110 --> 00:37:06,110
Silly boy.

518
00:37:06,590 --> 00:37:08,150
Well, well, Li He.

519
00:37:08,880 --> 00:37:10,480
You are silly indeed.

520
00:37:14,340 --> 00:37:19,900
(Renke Buns)

521
00:37:33,000 --> 00:37:35,320
Aunt, I want a meat bun
and a vegetable bun.

522
00:37:35,320 --> 00:37:36,280
And some black rice porridge.

523
00:37:42,670 --> 00:37:44,230
-One more red bean bun.
-Okay.

524
00:37:45,510 --> 00:37:46,590
I’ve paid the money, Aunt.

525
00:38:27,550 --> 00:38:28,320
Zeyu.

526
00:38:28,630 --> 00:38:29,880
Why are you here?

527
00:38:30,800 --> 00:38:32,320
I can’t rest assured to let you
go to school alone.

528
00:38:34,550 --> 00:38:36,710
But I left home
half an hour earlier today.

529
00:38:38,360 --> 00:38:39,480
I know with my knees

530
00:38:39,480 --> 00:38:42,510
that you will leave early
to avoid Li He.

531
00:38:47,360 --> 00:38:48,400
Well?

532
00:38:48,400 --> 00:38:50,400
Didn’t you leave early to avoid him?

533
00:38:50,710 --> 00:38:52,190
Now you want him to show up?

534
00:38:54,880 --> 00:38:55,480
Let’s go.

535
00:38:56,230 --> 00:38:56,840
Okay.

536
00:38:57,760 --> 00:38:58,760
Monitor!

537
00:39:00,840 --> 00:39:02,110
Let me carry the bag for you.

538
00:39:02,110 --> 00:39:03,440
It’s okay, I can carry it myself.

539
00:39:26,840 --> 00:39:29,910
♪Achoo I sneezed♪

540
00:39:29,990 --> 00:39:32,980
♪I’m not thinking of you secretly♪

541
00:39:33,090 --> 00:39:37,270
♪Your insolence overwhelms my calmness♪

542
00:39:39,650 --> 00:39:42,630
♪I don’t want to get close to you♪

543
00:39:42,730 --> 00:39:47,150
♪With declined immunity
I’m getting sick♪

544
00:39:52,450 --> 00:39:55,540
♪Achoo who’s missing me secretly♪

545
00:39:55,540 --> 00:39:58,650
♪You look even more lovely♪

546
00:39:58,820 --> 00:40:02,760
♪The world turns pink when I meet you♪

547
00:40:05,170 --> 00:40:08,340
♪I don’t know what to say but nonsense♪

548
00:40:08,340 --> 00:40:13,310
♪My heart beats together with yours♪

549
00:40:17,110 --> 00:40:18,630
♪Please listen♪

550
00:40:18,630 --> 00:40:24,450
♪Please stay ten meters away from me♪

551
00:40:25,260 --> 00:40:30,730
♪Or you may know my feelings for you♪

552
00:40:31,610 --> 00:40:33,900
